question:
What will be the output of the following code snippet?

```java
public class RecursionExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println(calculate(4));
    }
    public static int calculate(int n) {
        if (n == 1) {
            return 1;
        }
        return n + calculate(n - 1);
    }
}
```

Analyze the following recursive method for a potential issue:

```java
public static int fibonacci(int n) {
    if (n <= 1) {
        return n;
    }
    return fibonacci(n - 1) + fibonacci(n - 2);
}
```
What is the main inefficiency, and which technique could dramatically improve its performance for larger values of `n`?
